entries.title: Maryland Man Uses License Plate Numbers from Rude Driver for Lottery Game, Wins $500K Prize
entries.snippet: A Maryland man turned a frustrating road incident into a fortunate event by winning $500,000 in the lottery. The Glen Burnie resident used the license plate number of a car that had cut him off on the highway to play the Pick 5 lottery. He purchased 10 identical $1 tickets with the same number, each winning $50,000. The man, a technician, shared his joy with his mother and plans to use the money to pay bills and invest. The retailer, Doc's F&B Liquors, also received a $5,000 bonus for selling the winning tickets. This is not the first time a Maryland resident has won using license plate numbers; in 2023, a woman won $50,000 using the plate number of her new car.
